A father and young son sit together at a wooden kitchen table covered in scattered papers and pencils, viewed from above in warm golden afternoon light streaming through a window. The boy's hand hovers mid-air as if caught in the act of rushing, while the father gently points to a colorful hand-drawn mind map spread between them. The mind map shows interconnected bubbles and arrows in crayon colors—reds, blues, yellows—depicting a winding path with multiple stops. Their body language suggests a patient teaching moment, shoulders relaxed, heads tilted toward each other. Style: Studio Ghibli-inspired with soft watercolor textures, gentle cel-shading, warm domestic atmosphere, and that signature feeling of quiet everyday magic in ordinary moments.
